;\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n\n  // Read and execute schema\n  const schemaPath = join(dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url)), '..', 'schema.sql');\n  const schema = readFileSync(schemaPath, 'utf-8');\n  db.exec(schema);\n\n  return db;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: OT Engine (`src/ot.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ot.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\nThe OT engine supports two operation types: insert and delete. Each operation has a position, and either text (for insert) or count (for delete). The `transform` function ensures that when two concurrent operations are applied, they both take effect correctly.\n\n```typescript\nexport type Operation =\n  | { type: 'insert'; position: number; text: string }\n  | { type: 'delete'; position: number; count: number };\n\n// Transform op1 against op2 (both concurrent).\n// Returns transformed op1 that can be applied after op2.\nexport function transformOp(op1: Operation, op2: Operation): Operation {\n  // ... (full OT logic)\n}\n\nexport function applyOp(content: string, op: Operation): string {\n  // ... apply insert/delete to string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: REST Routes (`src/routes.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\nExpress router with:\n- `POST /documents` — create document (body: { title, content? })\n- `GET /documents` — list all documents\n- `GET /documents/:id` — get single document\n- `PUT /documents/:id` — update document (body: { title?, content? })\n- `DELETE /documents/:id` — delete document\n- `GET /documents/:id/versions` — get version history\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: WebSocket Collaboration (`src/websocket.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/websocket.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n- Parse document ID from WebSocket URL path (`/ws/documents/:id`)\n- On connection: verify document exists, send sync message with current content + version\n- On message: validate operation, transform against concurrent ops, apply, persist, broadcast\n- On close: clean up connection tracking\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Server Entry Point (`src/server.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/server.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\nFactory function `createApp(dbPath?)` that wires everything together and returns `{ app, start, stop }`.\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/__tests__/ot.test.ts`\n- Create: `src/__tests__/api.test.ts`\n- Create: `src/__tests__/websocket.test.ts`\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Build, Lint, Verify\n\nRun `npm run build`, `npm run lint`, `npm run test` and fix any issues.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
